      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKI SANZ (1) finished second last time out, beaten 5.5 metres, in a nice return to form at this track over 2200m. Has the benefit of a good draw. Finds a suitable assignment and will take plenty of beating once more. CEE TEE CHELSEA (2) has been racing well of late. Finished fifth at her latest appearance over 2200m here, beaten 7 metres. No excuses from this advantageous draw. Beautifully placed and is sure to be there at the finish. DONE WELL (4) was unplaced two starts ago then things went amiss last start when she broke and finished 24 metres away in ninth over 2090m at Hobart. Finds a nice race and can make up for that last start mishap. VICTORY GEORGE (7) was not beaten far last start when second over 2200m at this course. Ready to peak third-up from a spell and looks one for the multiples.",
